cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with visual recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of bilinear models and their comparison to existing state-of-the-art methods suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well. The experiments involve analyzing the effects of fine-tuning and the choice of two networks, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
